715970f-b.title: Manhattan: Amsterdam Avenue - 103rd Street (West)
715970f-b.text:
Amsterdam Ave., east side, north from west 103rd Street, showing
the Home for Respectable Aged Indigent Females occupying that block
front from 103rd to 1o4th Streets. Views 2 and 3 show details of this
area, with a Public School (No. 54) at the N.E. corner of 104th Street
and a Church (West End Presbyterian) at the N.E. corner of 105th Street.
November 7, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
